OL,3,CIan Paterson declines to take part in
OL,4,Cinquests, citing health and legal
OL,5,Cconcerns
OL,7,FHe was jailed in 2017 after being
OL,8,Fconvicted of 17 counts of wounding
OL,9,Fwith intent, and three counts of
OL,10,Funlawful wounding relating to
OL,11,Funnecessary operations performed on 10
OL,12,Fpatients between 1997 and 2011.
OL,14,FAn independent inquiry, chaired by
OL,15,Fformer Bishop of Norwich, the Right
OL,16,FRev Graham James, ruled in February
OL,17,F2020 that Paterson had carried out
OL,18,Fhundreds of unnecessary operations on
OL,19,Fscores of patients, exaggerating or
OL,20,Finventing cancer risks.
